  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This study systematically reviews STEM Teachers' Professional Development (TPD) programs in China, focusing on examining their objectives, methodologies, and outcomes.",
    "This research uncovers the best practices and persistent challenges that shape STEM education in China by highlighting key dimensions such as teacher efficacy, interdisciplinary integration, and regional disparities.",
    "Furthermore, it offers insights for global educational systems seeking to enhance STEM education through effective TPD models.",
    "In China's educational landscape, the \"13 th Five-Year Plan of Education and Information Technology,\" published by the Ministry of Education in June 2016, marked a significant milestone in STEM education (Ma, 2021; Zhong et al. 2022).",
    "As a result of this plan, STEM education has entered an exciting era, particularly in K-12 schools, signaling a paradigm shift toward an integrated and holistic approach to education (Felder, 2021; Hu, 2023)."
  ],
